The paper deals with the performance analysis of a drone cellular network, which involves communication and networking aspects (NI) as well as information theory (IT). The paper also considers different service models and uses mathematical tools to analyze the performance, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY) and mathematical analysis (MA). Additionally, the paper deals with mobility models, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC).
